      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(cost): recalculate usage cost if api returns confident zero (DeepSeek V4)",
        "body": "Fixes #97047\n\n**What Problem This Solves:**\nDeepSeek V4 (and some other providers) explicitly return \\usage.cost.total: 0\\ even when tokens are consumed. Because \\isModelPricingKnown\\ is true, the system skips recalculating the cost if it's explicitly 0, assuming it's accurate. This causes the Control UI Spend tracking to show \\.\n\n**Why This Change Was Made:**\nModified the fallback condition so that if \\entry.costTotal === 0\\ AND pricing is known AND tokens are > 0, it ignores the confident zero and calculates the estimate locally.\n\n**Evidence:**\nAdded a unit test reproducing the exact DeepSeek V4 API response structure and verified that the estimation runs correctly.",
